{{wikipedia|feto-maternal alloimmune thrombocytopenia}}

===Etymology===
Abbreviation of ''[[feto-maternal]] [[alloimmune]] [[thrombocytopenia]]''.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# {{lb|en|pathology}} A [[deficiency]] in the number of [[platelets]] in a [[fetus]]' [[blood]], due to the [[mother]]'s [[antibody|antibodies]] having been passed via the [[placenta]] and attacking the fetus' own platelets.

